# Use Bun

- Always use Bun for installs, dependency changes, scripts, and one-off binaries in this repo.
- Never suggest or run `npm`, `npx`, `yarn`, or `pnpm` commands.
- Preserve the existing Bun workflow and Bun lockfile already used by the project.

## Command examples

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
bun install
bun add <package>
bun remove <package>
bun run <script>
bun x <binary>

# ❌ BAD
npm install
npm run <script>
npx <binary>
yarn add <package>
pnpm add <package>
```

- When writing docs, fixes, or examples, convert package-manager commands to their Bun equivalents first.
- If external instructions assume another package manager, translate them to Bun before applying them.
